            "content": {
                "raw": "I generally like what you're doing here, but I have an idea to make install more transparent to the user.  What do you think about having installation still exist inside of install_script.sh, but just have a flag for \"install from conda\" or \"install from source\"?  That way, we don't have two separate text files running around that might confuse people who are trying to install as to which one they should use?  At the very least, if we do decide to keep two separate installer shell scripts, we might want to change the filenames to be something more descriptive like: \"install_script.sh\" becomes \"install_from_source.sh\" and \"get_yt.sh\" becomes \"install_from_conda.sh\" or something like that.  That doesn't necessarily have to be part of this PR, but it seems like we could at least discuss the idea here.",
                "html": "<p>I generally like what you're doing here, but I have an idea to make install more transparent to the user.  What do you think about having installation still exist inside of install_script.sh, but just have a flag for \"install from conda\" or \"install from source\"?  That way, we don't have two separate text files running around that might confuse people who are trying to install as to which one they should use?  At the very least, if we do decide to keep two separate installer shell scripts, we might want to change the filenames to be something more descriptive like: \"install_script.sh\" becomes \"install_from_source.sh\" and \"get_yt.sh\" becomes \"install_from_conda.sh\" or something like that.  That doesn't necessarily have to be part of this PR, but it seems like we could at least discuss the idea here.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
